                        <section class="s_text_image o_colored_level" data-name="Image - Text" data-snippet="s_image_text">
                            <div class="container">
                                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="13">
                                    <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item o_grid_item_image g-col-lg-7 order-lg-0 g-height-12 col-lg-7" style="grid-area: 2 / 1 / 14 / 8; z-index: 1; order: 1;">
                                        <img alt="" class="img img-fluid mx-auto o_we_custom_image rounded o_animate o_anim_fade_in o_anim_from_left o_animate_both_scroll o_animated" data-format-mimetype="image/webp" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-15.webp" data-resize-width="733" loading="eager" src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-15.webp" style="visibility: visible; --wanim-intensity: 14; animation-duration: 1.4s; animation-play-state: running;"/>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-5 o_we_padding_highlight col-lg-5 order-lg-0 g-height-9" style="grid-area: 5 / 8 / 14 / 13; z-index: 2; --grid-item-padding-y: 20px; order: 2;">
                                        <p>The story begins in <b><span class="text-o-color-1">1897</span></b>, when visionary hotelier <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Edmond Norris</span></b> , captivated by the untouched majesty of the Valais mountains, dreamt of creating a sanctuary unlike any other — a place where the rugged purity of the Alps would meet the grace and refinement of European hospitality.</p>
                                        <p>Guided by this vision, Norris chose a secluded plateau overlooking a pristine valley, where the silence of the pines mingled with the distant echo of cowbells. There, with the help of local craftsmen and artisans, he began to build what would become the <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Grand Norris Palace</span></b>.</p>
                                        <p>Each stone was carved from the surrounding cliffs, each beam of larch wood carried up the slopes by mule. The architecture blended <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Belle Époque elegance</span></b> with <b><span class="text-o-color-1">mountain authenticity</span></b>, creating an atmosphere that felt both majestic and deeply intimate.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_grid_item o_colored_level g-col-lg-5 g-height-3 col-lg-5 order-lg-0" style="grid-area: 2 / 8 / 5 / 13; z-index: 3; order: 0;">
                                        <div class="s_hr pt32 pb32 d-lg-none o_snippet_desktop_invisible" data-invisible="1" data-name="Separator" data-snippet="s_hr">
                                            <hr class="w-100 mx-auto" style="border-top-width: 0px;"/>
                                        </div>
                                        <h1 class="display-1" style="text-align: left;"><span class="h2-fs"><span style="color: rgb(198, 185, 179);">The story</span></span></h1>
                                        <h2 class="display-3-fs" style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: rgba(96, 70, 59, 0.74);"><strong>Grand Norris Palace</strong></span></h2>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section class="s_text_image o_colored_level pt64" data-name="Image - Text" data-snippet="s_image_text">
                            <div class="container">
                                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="12">
                                    <div class="o_grid_item o_grid_item_image o_grid_item_image_contain o_colored_level g-col-lg-7 g-height-11 col-lg-7 order-lg-0" style="grid-area: 2 / 6 / 13 / 13; z-index: 1; order: 0;">
                                        <img alt="" class="img img-fluid mx-auto o_we_custom_image o_animate o_anim_fade_in o_anim_from_right rounded o_animate_both_scroll o_animated" data-format-mimetype="image/webp" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-08.webp" data-resize-width="1920" loading="eager" src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-08.webp" style="--wanim-intensity: 10; animation-duration: 1.4s; visibility: visible; animation-play-state: running;"/>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_grid_item o_colored_level g-col-lg-5 g-height-6 col-lg-5 order-lg-0" style="grid-area: 6 / 1 / 12 / 6; z-index: 2; --grid-item-padding-y: 20px; order: 2;">
                                        <p>Perched high above the valley of <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Orsières</span></b>, in the enchanting <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Valais region</span></b> of Switzerland, the <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Grand Norris Palace</span></b> enjoys one of the most breathtaking settings in the Alps.&amp;nbsp;</p>
                                        <p>Surrounded by <span class="text-o-color-1"><b>snow-capped peaks, pine forests, and crystal-clear mountain lakes</b>,</span> the Palace overlooks a panorama that changes with every season <em>from the golden glow of autumn to the soft, shimmering silence of winter.</em></p>
                                        <p><strong><span class="text-o-color-1">The Grand Norris Palace</span></strong> is a place where <b><span class="text-o-color-1">luxury meets wilderness</span></b>, where silence becomes a form of poetry, and where every horizon reminds you how vast and beautiful the world can be.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_grid_item o_colored_level g-col-lg-6 g-height-3 col-lg-6 order-lg-0" style="grid-area: 3 / 1 / 6 / 7; z-index: 3; order: 1;">
                                        <h1 class="display-1" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 40px; color: rgb(198, 185, 179);">Our beloved</span><br/></h1>
                                        <h2 class="display-3-fs" style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: rgba(96, 70, 59, 0.74);"><strong>Swiss Alps</strong></span></h2>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section class="s_text_image o_colored_level pt48 pb48" data-name="Image - Text" data-snippet="s_image_text">
                            <div class="container">
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="o_colored_level offset-lg-2 col-lg-8 pb32">
                                        <p><img alt="" class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image mx-auto d-block" data-format-mimetype="image/webp" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-09.webp" data-resize-width="1920" loading="lazy" src="/hotel/static/src/img/content/website/hotel-image-09.webp" style="width: 100% !important;"/></p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_colored_level o_we_padding_highlight col-lg-6">
                                        <p>The estate lies at the crossroads of ancient mountain paths once used by shepherds and traders crossing into Italy. Today, it remains a place of quiet majesty, far from the noise of the world yet easily accessible from <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Verbier, Montreux, or Geneva</span></b>. Guests arrive along a winding alpine road that reveals, turn after turn, a landscape of pure wonder — until, at last, the turrets of the Grand Norris Palace emerge against the sky.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="o_colored_level col-lg-6">
                                        <p>Here, nature reigns supreme. Mornings begin with the scent of larch and the sound of distant waterfalls; evenings end under a canopy of stars untouched by city lights. The Palace's terraces open onto sweeping views of the <span class="text-o-color-1"><b>Mont Blanc massif</b></span> and the <b><span class="text-o-color-1">Trient Glacier</span></b>, offering a sense of peace that feels almost sacred.</p>
                                    </div>
